Product name: 1950s Nassau Vintage Metal Tin Toy Doll Stroller
Description:
1950s Nassau Vintage Metal Tin Toy Doll Stroller
Wonderful mid century metal doll stroller made by the Nassau Products Corporation out of Troy, N.Y. USA. A very nice display piece for a doll or antique toy collector. Fabricated out of heavy tin, this kid's doll stroller features a cream color enameled body with baby blue accents and light pink wheels. 
On the front bar there are 4 wooden beads that spin and move from side to side. The wheels roll smoothly and are fitted with heavy rubber tires. Back of seat is adorned with lithographed illustrations of six dancing dolls. Nassau company production info is printed on the side of the stroller.
Dimensions: Approximately 12" long x 9" wide and 8" high. 
CONDITION: Some light surface rust in a couple of spots, some scratches & scuffs but otherwise in great vintage condition. Note that it is missing the push handle.

Product name: SPRING SALE Boys Paw Patrol Patched Jeans Distressed Boys Jeans Boys Pants Paw Patrol Birthday
Description:
Description
"PAW patrol is on a roll!" and these jeans are perfect for your little fan of the show. Carefully selecting the print of each character for your little one, these jeans are designed to make any fan of the show excited. Our distressing techniques are sure to keep your young one in style with all the latest trends!
Unique
Every pair is up-cycled, distressed, and patched by hand. This makes each pair of Mountain Made Denim unique and individual. Since our products are one of a kind, the wash may vary between each product. That makes them made "just right" for you!
Versatility
Almost all our products are interchangeable, unless specified differently in the listing. So, if there is a special design of jeans/shorts that you want, but have another print of fabric in mind, let us know, and we would love to customize your very own pair! Please email us with any changes you have in mind.
Seasons 
Since we all want clothes for every season, each pair of jeans can be made into shorts, so your patchwork denim can be worn during all times of the year. Just shoot us an email and we can get to work on it for you. 
Sizes
Available in Boys & Girls, sizes 12 months to 5T. 
Larger Sizes
If you do not see a size that you would like, please email me. Shipping on larger sizes increases to 6.95 due to the weight of the extra denim. We ask that you order any size larger under "Custom Order".
Shipping
All jeans are custom made to order, and I am currently able to ship within 7-10 business days. Shipping costs are 4.14 for the first pair, and, 2.95 for each additional pair. If you would like them sooner, "Rush Order" (3-5 business days) is an option. Rush order shipping is 8.95, and 2.95 for each additional pair. 
Washing Instructions
Machine wash in cold water for best results. Do not apply direct heat. Hang or lay flat to dry. Drying in the dryer is at each customer's discretion, although it is not recommended as this could cause more fraying and distress on your pair of shorts/jeans. 
Your Vision
If you haven't found the exact patchwork design you are dreaming of, please email us with your idea. 
Thank you :)
Mychal Marcinko

Product name: Princess Leia Enamel Pin, Carrie Fisher, Pin Flair, Lapel Pin, Star Wars Pins, Hat Pin, Feminist Pins, Resistance, Rebel, Resist
Description:
⋆⋆⋆ A portion of all proceeds will be donated to charity (The International Bipolar Foundation).
⋆ 1.25-inch soft enamel pin
⋆ Black dye nickel plating
⋆ Single-post
⋆ Black rubber backing
⋆ Back stamped with "Edge of Print" logo
⋆ Shipped with a sturdy backing card in a bubble mailer
When we lost Carrie Fisher, I struggled to find a way to properly honor the woman who had such a huge influence on my life. I decided to make a pin to pay tribute to this bold and intelligent woman.
I also wanted to do something good in honor of her life as an activist and advocate for mental health awareness. A portion of all proceeds from this sale will go to The International Bipolar Foundation. Their mission is to eliminate Bipolar Disorder through the advancement of research, to promote and enhance care and support services, and to erase associated stigma through public education. In the first run of this pin, you helped raise 400 for The Thalians, a mental health advocacy group (Fisher's mom, the late Debbie Reynolds, was the president of the Thalians since 1957).
This pin is made from an illustration I drew of Fisher’s most famous role, Princess Leia, with her iconic A New Hope styling. It was a role with which Fisher had a complicated relationship, as detailed in her many memoirs. "I've sort of melded with her over time," she told Terry Gross in an interview on NPR in November. "The downside is the hair and some of the outfits. But I like Princess Leia. I like how she handles things. I like how she treats people. I- she tells the truth. She, you know, gets what she wants done."
Carrie Fisher gave us Princess Leia by mining pieces of her own personality to create one of the most important characters of all time. "I'm more of an archaeologist. I play what I am. I dig what I can. It's a character that's not too far from myself, except I don't have any laser guns," she said. Thank you for helping me honor this great soul and her life of advocacy and empowerment.
 Please follow me on Instagram for updates! @edgeofprint http://www.instragram.com/edgeofprint
